  ('CISA-01212', 5, 'Medium', 'Vulnerability Management', 'Which action is MOST critical for the auditor to recommend regarding vulnerability management in this new environment?', 'Prioritize vulnerability scanning of legacy systems to ensure they do not become entry points for attacks targeting the 5G network.', 'Implement a vulnerability disclosure program to encourage external researchers to report vulnerabilities in the 5G infrastructure.', 'Develop and implement a vulnerability management process specifically tailored to the unique characteristics of SDN and NFV technologies.', 'Increase the frequency of penetration testing on the 5G network to proactively identify vulnerabilities before they can be exploited.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Develop and implement a vulnerability management process specifically tailored to the unique characteristics of SDN and NFV technologies.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit tra