  ('CISA-01228', 5, 'Medium', 'Vulnerability Management', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to address the scope limitation of the vulnerability assessment?', 'Prioritize the assessment of external components and postpone assessment of internal systems until additional budget becomes available.', 'Expand the vulnerability assessment to include the integration points between the customer portal and the core policy administration system.', 'Implement compensating controls, such as intrusion detection systems, to protect the core policy administration system.', 'Reduce the frequency of vulnerability assessments to cover the entire system within the existing budget.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Expand the vulnerability assessment to include the integration points between the customer portal and the core policy administration system.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for futur