  ('CISA-01233', 5, 'Medium', 'Incident Investigation and Forensics', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to management?', 'Immediately isolate the affected server and rebuild it from a known good backup.', 'Prioritize containment and preservation of evidence on the affected server while continuing the investigation.', 'Run a vulnerability scan on all servers within the student information system network segment.', 'Immediately notify all students whose data might have been compromised, in accordance with the data breach notification policy.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Prioritize containment and preservation of evidence on the affected server while continuing the investigation.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Immediately isolate the affected server and rebuild it from a known good backup. →