  ('CISA-01256', 5, 'Hard', 'Incident Investigation and Forensics', 'What is the auditor''s MOST important recommendation to improve the clinic''s incident response capabilities?', 'Implement a comprehensive security awareness training program for all employees to prevent future phishing attacks.', 'Establish a formal, documented incident response plan with clearly defined roles, responsibilities, and procedures.', 'Invest in advanced threat intelligence feeds to proactively identify and block malicious emails.', 'Immediately report the incident to all affected patients to maintain transparency and build trust.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a formal, documented incident response plan with clearly defined roles, responsibilities, and procedures.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement a