  ('CISA-01275', 5, 'Hard', 'Cloud and Infrastructure Security', 'What is the MOST important control the auditor should recommend to address this risk?', 'Implement role-based access control (RBAC) within the cloud environment to restrict access to the machine learning models and associated data.', 'Establish a data governance framework that includes data lineage tracking to ensure the integrity and traceability of the data used to train the machine learning models.', 'Conduct regular penetration testing of the cloud environment to identify vulnerabilities in the machine learning infrastructure.', 'Implement data masking techniques to anonymize sensitive data before it is used to train the machine learning models.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a data governance framework that includes data lineage tracking to ensure the integrity and traceability of the data used to train the machine learning models.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountabil