  ('CISA-01291', 5, 'Hard', 'Insider Threat and Privacy Protection', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to mitigate the risk of insider threats impacting production data integrity?', 'Implement multi-factor authentication (MFA) for all ERP system users, regardless of their role or access privileges.', 'Conduct a comprehensive review of privileged access management (PAM) controls, focusing on segregation of duties and least privilege principles.', 'Deploy a data loss prevention (DLP) solution to monitor and prevent unauthorized exfiltration of sensitive production data.', 'Perform background checks on all employees with access to the ERP system, including temporary staff and contractors.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct a comprehensive review of privileged access management (PAM) controls, focusing on segregation of duties and least privilege principles.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for complianc