  ('CISA-01292', 5, 'Hard', 'Insider Threat and Privacy Protection', 'What is the auditor''s PRIMARY concern regarding the mitigation of future insider-assisted cyber incidents?', 'The technical effectiveness of endpoint detection and response (EDR) solutions on OT systems.', 'The maturity of the organization''s security awareness training program, including targeted training for high-risk departments like engineering.', 'The comprehensiveness of the incident response plan for OT systems, including defined roles and responsibilities.', 'The rigor of vulnerability scanning and patching processes for OT systems, including timely remediation of identified vulnerabilities.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): The maturity of the organization''s security awareness training program, including targeted training for high-risk departments like engineering.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for f