  ('CISA-01295', 5, 'Hard', 'Insider Threat and Privacy Protection', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to mitigate the risk of insider threats and data breaches in this scenario?', 'Implementing multi-factor authentication for all data science team members accessing the transaction monitoring system.', 'Developing and implementing a comprehensive data access governance framework, including role-based access controls, data masking techniques, and regular access reviews.', 'Conducting background checks on all data science team members who have access to sensitive customer transaction data.', 'Deploying data loss prevention (DLP) tools to monitor and prevent unauthorized exfiltration of sensitive customer transaction data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Developing and implementing a comprehensive data access governance framework, including role-based access controls, data masking techniques, and regular access reviews.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear