  ('CISA-01325', 1, 'Medium', 'Ethics', 'What is the PRIMARY ethical responsibility of the information systems auditor in this scenario?', 'Immediately report the offending students to the university disciplinary board to ensure swift punishment.', 'Disclose the specific details of the file-sharing activity to the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA).', 'Assess the effectiveness of the university''s controls in detecting and preventing policy violations, and report findings to management.', 'Ignore the activity since students have a right to privacy on the university''s open network.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Assess the effectiveness of the university''s controls in detecting and preventing policy violations, and report findings to management.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Immediately report the offending students to the university disciplinary board to ensure swift punishment. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option B: Disclose the specific details of the file-sharing activity to the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA). → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Ignore the activity since students have a right to privacy on the university''s open network. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.', 'The primary ethical responsibility of the auditor is to evaluate the controls in place and report on their effectiveness to management. This promotes accountability and allows for improvement of security measures. The auditor''s role is not to punish or directly enforce policy but to provide assurance on the governance and controls.', 'See reasoning above for explanation of correct vs incorrect choices', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Assess the effectiveness of the university''s controls in detecting and preventing policy violations, and report findings to management.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the