t practices. → While seemingly reasonable, this approach deviates from best practice and creates unnecessary risk or inefficiency.'),
  ('CISA-01344', 2, 'Medium', 'KPIs', 'Which of the following KPIs would be MOST effective in measuring IT''s contribution to improving patient satisfaction?', 'Number of IT projects completed on time and within budget.', 'Percentage of patient feedback scores related to technology usability.', 'Uptime percentage of the hospital''s electronic health record (EHR) system.', 'Number of help desk tickets resolved within service level agreements (SLAs).', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Percentage of patient feedback scores related to technology usability.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer represents the best practice approach for the scenario presented. It aligns with ISACA standards, COBIT framework principles, and proven audit methodologies. The reasoning is grounded in risk management fundamentals and control design best practices.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: In a typical enterprise scenario, the organization that follows this answer''s approach achieves better outcomes. For instance, proper implementation results in: • Reduced operational risk • Better compliance with regulations • Improved stakeholder confidence • More efficient resource allocation • Better decision-making with proper information  The alternative approaches lead to gaps, inefficiencies, or increased risk.  WHY THIS MATTERS: Adopting this best practice ensures: • Alignment with industry standards • Reduced risk of audit findings • Better business-technology outcomes • More effective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Number of IT projects completed on time and within budget. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Uptime percentage of the hospital''s electronic health record (EHR) system. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It might address part of the issue but misses the full picture.  Option D: Number of help desk tickets resolved within